<title>Math Operators in Scripting</title>
<section>
<title>Objective and Overview</title>
<para>The objective of this reference article is to inform GMAT users of the Math Operators available to them and their syntax in scripting. </para>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>i.e. -+GMAT MyVar = 5 + 6 * sqrt(4)+-)</para></listitem>
</itemizedlist>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>l examples assume variables and arrays, MyVar* and MyArr*, have already been created.</para></listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</section>
<section>
<title>Addition</title>
<para>-+GMAT MyVar = 4 + 5;+-</para>
</section>
<section>
<title>Subtraction</title>
<para>-+GMAT MyVar = 3 - 1;+-</para>
</section>
<section>
<title>Division</title>
<para>-+GMAT MyVar = 8 / 2;+-</para>
</section>
<section>
<title>Multiplication</title>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>+GMAT MyVar = 12 * 2;+-</para></listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</section>
<section>
<title>Exponentiation</title>
<para>-+GMAT MyVar = 2 ^ 2;+-</para>
</section>
